    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-02-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-02-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="502"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Romero</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-02-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 25, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have had the honor to receive your note of the
                    23d instant, relative to an alleged forcible taking from the jurisdiction of the
                    Mexican tribunals, by Acting Rear-Admiral Wilkes, of the steamer Noe-Daquy,
                    captured by the authorities of Yucatan for being engaged in the slave trade.</p>
                <p>In reply, I have the honor to acquaint you that a translation of your
                    communication will be at once submitted to the Secretary of the Navy, with a
                    request for an inquiry into the case, with a view to such further proceedings as
                    the result may be found to call for.</p>
                <p>I avail myself of the occasion, sir, to offer you a renewed assurance of my very
                    high consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Señor Don <hi rend="smallcaps">Matias Romero</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
